      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Brilliant mare CAPTAINS MISTRESS NZ (1) took her record at the Menangle mile to six from seven when coming from wider to land a similar race to this last start. Blessed with abundant speed and she'll get to use it from the inside draw. The one to beat. DON HUGO (5) was a terrific third from the outside barrier when last seen in the Miracle Mile in March. Hasn't missed a place in 16 tries at the circuit and distance, winning eight. Two-time fresh winner and a trial win suggests he is back in good order. HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (2) has 3.3m to make up on Captains Mistress through the last-start second but he draws much lower and he is another who loves racing over the mile here. RIPP (3) led from wider to find winning form last start. This is tougher but he draws well so is a first four hope.",
